P. 9, l. 34. Laurenti. It is perhaps hardly necessary to remark, in explanation of these lines, that St. Laurence suffered martyrdom on a gridiron (eraticula). He held the office of treasurer of the church of Rome, and having distributed the wealth of the church among the poor, he presented these to the pagan emperor who ordered him to deliver up the treasures.
